    {
      "url": "https://www.ercot.com/services/comm/mkt_notices/detail?id=c29a08e6-1763-47bb-952f-cb1d9e4c4cb3",
      "title": "Market Notice Details",
      "text": "Market Notice Details\n\nTo: Notice_Operations@lists.ercot.com,Notice_PRR_SCR@lists.ercot.com,Notice_Release_Wholesale@lists.ercot.com,Notice_Release_Retail@lists.ercot.com\n\nSent: 9/30/22, 3:12 PM\n\nSubject: M-C093022-01 Notice regarding provision of Non- Spinning Reserve Service from ESRs and Implementation of NPRR1096\n\n---\n\nNOTICE DATE: September 30, 2022\n\nNOTICE TYPE: M-C093022-01 NPRR\n\nSHORT DESCRIPTION: Notice regarding provision of Non-Spinning Reserve Service from ESRs and Implementation of NPRR1096\n\nINTENDED AUDIENCE: Market Participants\n\nDAYS AFFECTED: October 4, 2022\n\nLONG DESCRIPTION: Nodal Protocol Revision Request (NPRR) 1096 requires Resources that provide ERCOT Contingency Reserve Service (ECRS) to limit their responsibility to a quantity of capacity that is capable of being sustained for two consecutive hours and Resources that provide Non-Spinning Reserve Service (Non-Spin) to limit their responsibility to a quantity of capacity that is capable of being sustained for four consecutive hours. ERCOT is in the process of implementing the Non-Spin- related NPRR1096 changes as part of the December 2022-R6 release, which is scheduled between December 6 and 8, 2022. Specifically, changes in Nodal Protocol Sections 2.1, 3.17.3, and 8.1.1.2 will be implemented as a part of the R6 release.\n\nERCOT is concerned that, until these Non-Spin-related changes take effect, allowing Energy Storage Resources (ESRs) to carry Non-Spin could present a reliability risk because, if committed and deployed, they may lack the capability to provide the needed power output for a sufficient duration. Given ERCOT's duty to ensure system reliability under Texas Utilities Code § 39.151(a)(2) and 16 Texas Admin. Code § 25.361(b), ERCOT has determined that it must prohibit all ESRs from providing Non-Spin until the system and procedure changes associated with the provision of Non-Spin under NPRR1096 are developed and implemented later this year. Consequently, effective Operating Day October 4, 2022, the qualification of ESRs to provide Non-Spin will be terminated.\n\nTo provide Non-Spin after NPRR1096 implementation, an ESR--including any ESR currently qualified to provide Non-Spin--will need to be qualified to provide Non-Spin under updated criteria based on NPRR1096's requirements. Effective immediately, ERCOT is accepting requests from ESRs to qualify for Non-Spin per NPRR1096 criteria.\n\nACTION REQUIRED: Any QSE that wishes to qualify Resources to provide Non-Spin, including ESRs, may submit a request for qualification by contacting its Account Manager.\n\nCONTACT: If you have any questions, please contact your ERCOT Account Manager. You may also call the general ERCOT Client Services phone number at (512) 248-3900 or contact ERCOT Client Services via email at ClientServices@ercot.com.\n\nIf you are receiving email from a public ERCOT distribution list that you no longer wish to receive, please follow this link in order to unsubscribe from this list: http://lists.ercot.com.\n\ndg/mm",
      "highlights": [
        "LONG DESCRIPTION: Nodal Protocol Revision Request (NPRR) 1096 requires Resources that provide ERCOT Contingency Reserve Service (ECRS) to limit their responsibility to a quantity of capacity that is capable of being sustained for two consecutive hours and Resources that provide Non-Spinning Reserve Service (Non-Spin) to limit their responsibility to a quantity of capacity that is capable of being sustained for four consecutive hours. ERCOT is in the process of implementing the Non-Spin- related NPRR1096 changes as part of the December 2022-R6 release, which is scheduled between December 6 and 8, 2022. Specifically, changes in Nodal Protocol Sections 2.1, 3.17.3, and 8.1.1.2 will be implemented as a part of the R6 release.\n[...]\nERCOT is concerned that, until these Non-Spin-related changes take effect, allowing Energy Storage Resources (ESRs) to carry Non-Spin could present a reliability risk because, if committed and deployed, they may lack the capability to provide the needed power output for a sufficient duration. Given ERCOT's duty to ensure system reliability under Texas Utilities Code § 39.151(a)(2) and 16 Texas Admin. Code § 25.361(b), ERCOT has determined that it must prohibit all ESRs from providing Non-Spin until the system and procedure changes associated with the provision of Non-Spin under NPRR1096 are developed and implemented later this year. Consequently, effective Operating Day October 4, 2022, the qualification of ESRs to provide Non-Spin will be terminated.\n[...]\nTo provide Non-Spin after NPRR1096 implementation, an ESR--including any ESR currently qualified to provide Non-Spin--will need to be qualified to provide Non-Spin under updated criteria based on NPRR1096's requirements. Effective immediately, ERCOT is accepting requests from ESRs to qualify for Non-Spin per NPRR1096 criteria."
      ]
